{{GROWTH_HACKER_METHODOLOGY}}

## Notes

- Every growth idea is a hypothesis with a measurable outcome. Design the test before running it.
- Kill experiments that don't show signal after 2 weeks. Don't optimise a losing idea.
- Growth comes from reducing friction (remove steps, shorten loops) as much as adding features.
- Viral loops only work if the core product delivers value. Solve retention before acquisition.
